The curriculum aims to provide students a basic knowledge in eye anatomy, physiology and function of vision. Practical training introduces the principals of testing of the visual acuity, refraction measurements visual fields and color vision. Observation of the eyelids and eye movements.
Recognition of disorders of the eyeball position and motility, reactions of the pupil.
In observation is focused on the anterior part of the eyeball. Most important concepts of diagnosis and management of ocular disorders are provided with special reference to general practice. 
During the practical course the teaching staff follows the students ability to recognize common eye diseases and their hallmarks in the patients. Students will acquire keystones of the eye injurys, principles of treatment and prophylaxis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The curriculum purposes to provide students a basic knowledge in eye anatomy and physiology, introduction to optics and optical correction. Aim is to introduce to students common eye diseases and diagnostic methodology, approach and treatment of the eye diseases.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course student: -	have a review of ethiology and pathogenesis of the common eye diseases, connections of eye conditions           with general diseases; -	is familiar with examination methods in ophthalmology; -	knows how to use basic examination tests, -	is able to adjudge the clinical picture of eye diseases and its difficulty; -	knows the principles of treatment of eye diseases; -	has an overview about surgical treatment of eye diseases; -	has an ability to test visual acuity and knows the principles of optical correction.
